article.headline: Idaho State 75, Montana State 64
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. (AP) -- Doug D'Amore hit all eight of his 3-point attempts and scored a career-high 28 points to lead Idaho State to a 75-64 win over Montana State Saturday night. D'Amore, whose previous career-best was 13 points, finished the game 9-of-12 from the field. He also had nine rebounds and four assists. D'Amore did most of his damage early, hitting four consecutive 3s to put the Bengals ahead 17-6 less than five minutes into the game. ISU (7-10, 2-1 Big Sky) took its biggest lead on a Scott Henry putback that made it 22-6 with 14:49 left in the half. The Bobcats (10-7, 2-2) closed the half with a 31-12 run, including four unanswered points by Calvin Ento, to take a 37-34 halftime lead. The Bengals started the second half with an 8-0 run to regain a 42-37 lead. ISU eventually took a 50-42 lead before a 6-0 Bobcat spurt brought MSU back to within two at 50-48 with 12:19 to play. But that was as close as the Cats would get. The Bengals answered with a 7-0 run for a 57-48 lead at the 8:57 mark. Idaho State led by as many as 13 in the second half. Jason Erickson led the Bobcats with 18 points and Ento finished with 10 points and seven rebounds. Henry finished with 13 points and eight rebounds for ISU, while Jeff Gardner added 11 points and Jesse Smith 10.
